OL,7,F"But when you have children that are
OL,8,Fnow eight or nine years old, they are
OL,9,Flooking at TikTok, they're looking at
OL,10,Fsocial media and there are people
OL,11,Fclaiming that the harm that was caused
OL,12,Fto them or their sibling was not
OL,13,Fcaused by somebody who's been found
OL,14,Fguilty of those crimes by a jury and
OL,15,Fwhose appeals have been exhausted, and
OL,16,Fthe Court of Appeal have also said she
OL,17,Fremains guilty of these crimes."
